/*
Packer before 1.7.6 suffers from stack-based buffer overflow. The binary generates
packer templates off local files, takes user-supplied arguments to fill these templates,
and executes user-supplied commands using these templates. These three command
line arguments to the "validate" subcommand - "var-file", "var", and "var-default" can
be used to provide user-supplied input into the templates. If the length of the value
supplied to one of these flags is large enough, a stack-based buffer overflow will
occur.


Affected versions

Packer versions prior to v1.7.6

Remediation

Upgrade to Packer version 1.7.6 or later.

Credits

This issue was responsibly disclosed by AppsmartUSA.


Reference
